think First act on the new model was to confirm repo state, not assume it. Found two uncommitted modifications — old/README.md and vere/old/README.md — the exact files a prior turn had accidentally overwritten. Diffed before touching: HEAD/committed held the correct original Urbit READMEs, but the working tree held stray duplicate copies of the fork-notes content that already lives (committed) in FORK_NOTES.md.
